This paper focuses on privacy protection in Participatory Sensing, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a privacy-enhanced infrastructure for mobile phone users, which suggests a possible sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses open problems and possible research directions, which could fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CY), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB).
